.TH TRANSCRIBE-DIARIZE 1 "April 2026" "dictee 1.3.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
transcribe-diarize \- transcribe with speaker identification
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B transcribe-diarize
.I audio_file
.RI [ model_dir ]
.RI [ sortformer_dir ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B transcribe-diarize
transcribes audio and identifies who is speaking (up to 4 speakers).
Uses Parakeet TDT for transcription and Sortformer for speaker diarization.
.PP
Supports 25 languages (TDT). Diarization is language-independent.
.PP
Accepts any audio format (MP3, OGG, FLAC, OPUS, etc.) via automatic
.BR ffmpeg (1)
conversion to WAV 16kHz mono.
File paths support
.BR ~ ", " ./ ", and " ../
resolution.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I audio_file
Path to audio file (required). Any format supported by ffmpeg is accepted.
.TP
.I model_dir
Path to TDT model (default: /usr/share/dictee/tdt).
.TP
.I sortformer_dir
Path to Sortformer model (default: /usr/share/dictee/sortformer).
.TP
.BR \-\-help ", " \-h
Display a brief usage summary and exit.
.SH OUTPUT
.PP
[0.00s \- 2.50s] Speaker 0: Hello, how are you?
.br
[2.60s \- 5.30s] Speaker 1: I'm fine, thanks!
.SH BUILD
This binary requires the
.B sortformer
Cargo feature:
.PP
.RS
cargo build \-\-release \-\-features sortformer
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR transcribe (1),
.BR transcribe\-stream\-diarize (1),
.BR ffmpeg (1)
.SH AUTHOR
rcspam <rcspams@gmail.com>
